            "title": "LSEG to help upgrade Australian bourse operator ASX's derivatives trading platform",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>March 4 (Reuters) - The London Stock Exchange Group said on Wednesday that it would help upgrade Australian exchange operator ASX's  derivatives market trading platform as part of a partnership deal. </p><p>\n              Under the deal, LSEG will provide a high-performance, low-latency system for ASX 24, which offers trading in Australian and New Zealand equity, commodity and interest rate derivatives, including futures and options.</p><!-- Article --><p>\n              The upgrade would enable the Australian exchange operator to expand ASX 24's product offerings and respond to increasing sophistication in global derivatives trading, LSEG said.</p><p>\n              The deal comes against the backdrop of a major technology overhaul to upgrade ASX's ageing settlement systems, which have been blamed for several trading outages.</p><p>\n              Farid Sammur, ASX's head of markets technology, said the overhaul was a \"critical investment\" in the long-term strength of Australia's derivatives markets, adding that the platform would support innovation and evolving customer needs.</p><p>\n              Reuters is a news provider for LSEG's Workspace terminal  and other products.</p><p>\n               (Reporting by Roshan Thomas and Prerna Bedi in Bengaluru; Editing by Anil D'Silva)</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.marketscreener.com/news/lseg-to-help-upgrade-australian-bourse-operator-asx-s-derivatives-trading-platform-ce7e5cd3df89f722",
